==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jabber
<hw>Jab"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Jabbered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Jabbering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. <er>Gibber</er>,
<er>Gabble</er>.]</ety> <def>To talk rapidly, indistinctly, or
unintelligibly; to utter gibberish or nonsense; to chatter.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jabber</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Jabber
<hw>Jab"ber</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To utter rapidly or
indistinctly; to gabble; <as>as, to <ex>jabber</ex> French</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jabber</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Jabber
<hw>Jab"ber</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Rapid or incoherent talk, with
indistinct utterance; gibberish.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jabberer</ent>⟦br⟧
